Writing regularly to $4011 allows you to play 7-bit WAVs on the NES/Famicom without bothering with extra audio, but unfortunately this typically takes 100% of CPU time.<br /><br />Altough there should be a way to write a normal programm in a maneer so that it can interupt each constant amount of cycles to play the next WAV sample, this sounds extremely tedious to do.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Jan 03, 2009 3:26 am</p><hr />
