<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4691&amp;p=41242#p41242</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4691&amp;p=41242#p41242"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Question: WAV - Mapper]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4691&amp;p=41242#p41242"><![CDATA[
I know how "play this MP3 file" could be made into a physical mapper: have the cart control a CD player. A CD player's remote control uses a serial protocol over a wired or infrared physical layer. So we just have to emulate a serial port, and the mapper turns this into commands to a (real or emulated) CD player.<br /><br />Or if you're willing to accept a 7 percent slowdown, you can use DPCM to play back a long sample within the ROM file. A long time ago, I made a <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/max-300.zip" class="postlink">demo</a> that plays "Max 300", a song from DDR, through a common mapper.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Jan 02, 2009 6:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
